         <abstract>
            <p>An algorithm is given for deciding whether a closed geodesic on a finite-sheeted cover of the modular surface has self-intersections; if it does, the algorithm gives them in the order they occur in traversing the geodesic. The following general result on geodesics is proved: any closed geodesic on a Riemann surface $R$ can be lifted to a simple closed geodesic on some finite-sheeted cover of $R$. In the last two sections the connection with the stabilizer (under the modular group) of a Markov quadratic irrationality is discussed.</p>
          </abstract>
